title: Ximo Tebar - The Jazz Guitar Trio Vol 1 to 4 - Jazz Organ
description:
Ximo Tebar - The Jazz Guitar Trio Vol 1 to 4 - Jazz Organ

Ximo Tebar was born in Valencia, Spain, in 1963, and at the age of seven began playing the guitar, first studying flamenco. At seventeen he decided to turn professional, and since then has performed in concerts and recordings in Spain, Europe and America, leading his own group or accompanying prestigious soloists, featuring amongst others: Johnny Griffin, Benny Golson, Eddie Henderson, Tete Montoliu, Lou Donaldson, Lou Bennett, Louie Bellson, Dr. Lonnie Smith, Joey DeFrancesco, etc.

Included albums in cronological recorded order:
1992 Ximo Tebar - The Jazz Guitar Trio Vol 1 - Hello Mr. Bennett
1997 Ximo Tebar - The Jazz Guitar Trio Vol 2 - So What
1998 Ximo Tebar - The Jazz Guitar Trio Vol 3 - Goes Blue
1999 Ximo Tebar - The Jazz Guitar Trio Vol 4 - The Champs

--------

The Jazz Guitar Trio Vol 1 - Lou Bennett at the organ
The Jazz Guitar Trio Vol 2 - Lonnie Smith at the organ
The Jazz Guitar Trio Vol 3 - Lonnie Smith at the organ
The Jazz Guitar Trio Vol 4 - Joey DeFrancesco at the organ

--------

Format: MP3 320 kbit/s. All songs are tagged by the book.
